  <Name>conversations\00_stronghold\00_recruits\00_cv_vendrienswell_skilltrainer_heraldrhogalus</Name>
  <NextEntryID>1</NextEntryID>
  <EntryCount>84</EntryCount>
  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>The Fatebinder, a tall man with slumped shoulders and a hawkish nose, blinks at you with eyes tired from scanning hundreds of manuscript pages. 

"Ah, [Player Name], you resume your place among us at last. You are quite a sight for these sore eyes."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I've activated the Spire in [url=glossary:vendrien's well]Vendrien's Well[/url]. You should see it."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What might I teach you on this fine occasion? How about a strike of fire from the firmaments? How about the necrosis of a liar's tongue?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I would study its secrets if you'll allow. Yes, I am most eager to examine the apex of a Spire. Most curious that you were able to access one."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>Bank Node 11</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Control the magic, do not let the magic control you. If you struggle in this area, rely on the Archon you've invoked to strengthen and guide the spell's form as you shape it."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Memorize your sigils in both name and movement if you wish to strength the impact of your spells. Strengthen the impact of your spells if you wish to avoid having your bowels ripped out in battle."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I could demonstrate for you one of [url=glossary:bleden mark]Bleden Mark[/url]'s more intricate shadow spells if you're feeling especially dexterous. Perpetual loss of sight due to magical misfire is only a middling risk."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>"There have been three known Archons of Fire throughout the ages. You will want to study each of their forms if you wish to fully master the element. Of course, to properly study one would consume the whole of a lifetime."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Occasionally there lies a thread of knowledge for which I wish I could forget. Your recent actions come to mind, for example."

"[url=glossary:vendrien's well]Vendrien's Well[/url] has made you an anomaly to us. And yet I'm curious to learn about the Tiers." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You look as if you have questions for me to untangle. Ask. I am feeling generous." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Tell me about some of the past Archons."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Where did you study when you were younger?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What do you think about the other Fatebinders?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Can you tell me about the Oldwalls and the Bane?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>Bank Node 22</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Nox Mirea, the Archon of Pestilence, was disliked in her circles. When she opened her eyes to see, and her mouth to speak, it is said that flies would gust into the air, swarming so thick as to blacken the sky. She died in the twentieth year of her birth, following a string of unusual and grotesque symptoms."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Rin, the second Archon of Lightning, often struggled to control the power that roiled within him. If he suffered but a single slip of concentration, he risked an instant electrocution to his touch. Or so he claimed after killing the first Archon of Water during a diplomatic embrace."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>25</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Much that was known has been lost regarding the first Archon of Frost, but his talents were improved upon by three following Archons - sisters born together and never since seen apart. It is said, Ranna, Nirabel, and Slayr were so cold at birth that they were thought stillborn."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>26</ID>
      <DefaultText>"No one is entirely sure how many Archons [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] has killed, but I would guess it numbers several dozen or more based on the various histories I've been able to piece together."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>27</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I've been a ward of the Court for as long as I've been aware. As a child, I demonstrated wholly perfect recall, and I absorbed all that [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url] and my tutors had to offer."

"I remember hating all the lectures and wishing I could learn at my pace. Funny how I envied the Sages of the Tiers, how they could spend their whole lives reading and never exhaust their library."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>28</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You'll need to be more specific than that, I'm afraid. There is, on last count, slightly more than a handful of us."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>29</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What's your opinion of the Fatebinder of War?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>30</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What's your opinion of the Fatebinder of Balance?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>31</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What's your opinion of me?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>32</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Let's talk about something else."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>33</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'd like to know more about the Tiers."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>34</ID>
      <DefaultText>"With which should I start?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>35</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Tell me about the Oldwalls."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>36</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Tell me about the Bane."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>37</ID>
      <DefaultText>"We know little enough about the ancient structures, save that they pre-date all historical record. The forbidding ruins crisscrossed the Tiers and North alike centuries before we raised our cities." 

"The only one old enough to guess is likely [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>38</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The Bane are found in the Oldwalls, but much of their defining qualities still escape me. They are creatures of smoke, claw, and fang. If you find yourself unfortunate enough to fight one, remember that spells are effective against them, but grab the attention of others lurking near."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>39</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The political entities of the Tiers are essentially split between the Bastard Tier, the [url=glossary:younger realms]Younger Realms[/url], and the Free Cities. Of which would you like to know?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>40</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What can you tell me about the Bastard Tier?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>41</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm curious to know more about the [url=glossary:younger realms]Younger Realms[/url]."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>42</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I would like to hear about the Free Cities."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>43</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I want to talk about the Sages."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>44</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The Bastard Tier is the most northern of the Tiers and was the first to bow to [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' reign, though the knee they bent fell unwillingly. [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] had his eye on the Bastard Tier for many years before he marched on her capital city."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>45</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The [url=glossary:younger realms]Younger Realms[/url] sprawl the middle and southern-most Tiers and can be cataloged as follows: Apex, Azure, Haven, and Stalwart."

"Azure was renowned for its exceptionally fertile land which fed the whole of the Tiers. That was before [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url] of Stone blighted the land."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>46</ID>
      <DefaultText>"There are three Free Cities remaining - Last Harbor, Spiral's Maw, and Baris-in-Chains. The first and strongest of the Free Cities was the Setting Sun, which [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] crushed in 429 with the [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url] of Tumult. After that, the remaining Free Cities were quick to surrender."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>47</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I heard rumors that you have slain Renata." The Fatebinder rubs an ink-stained thumb against his left temple as if to work away the lingering weariness. "She was a horrid, manipulative woman who contributed to ceaseless migraines with her incessant correspondence, so I find myself surprisingly pleased at the news. I assume she gave you just cause for quarrel."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>48</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I hear you have met Renata. My condolences to you." The Fatebinder of [url=glossary:lore]Lore[/url] shakes his head as if to clear a distasteful memory. "I would not complain if you had killed her."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>49</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I will not speak of the Sages. They are no better than charlatans and cons, wholly selfish in their ill pursuit to hoard all knowledge from others. They are self-blinded by their own deceptions and clever manipulations. They alone caused their own undoing and are solely to blame for the [url=glossary:burning library]Burning Library[/url] - one of the most grievous of wrongs in the known histories for which they can never be forgiven."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>50</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Let us begin a new age of knowledge and understanding. If we cannot see the mysteries of the Archons revealed, we must at least strive to master the arts of their legacy."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>51</ID>
      <DefaultText>"An old mage once told me, 'How can the fruit of practice hope to ripen if not first a seed of knowledge is sown?' I thumped him in the throat with my staff."

The Fatebinder crosses his arms into the sleeves of his robe and levels you with a withering stare. 

"I will not humor fools who can only expound through adages and riddles."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>52</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Have patience when practicing a new form, lest your fingers falter and fail. A hasty invocation brings with it a greater risk than you can know."

The Fatebinder of [url=glossary:lore]Lore[/url] tips his head in measured thought.

"Or at the least, practice fifteen paces away from me - over there."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>53</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Of course, now the [url=glossary:vellum citadel]Vellum Citadel[/url] is nothing more than a burning waste."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>54</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Nunoval's keen, brash, and a hearty braggart with a fondness for bloodshed. He can be utterly unbearable at times."

"His justice is fair, even if he skews toward rather exacting and uncompromising punishments at times." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>55</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Calio is the finest among us. Her discernment is beyond reproach, and she is perhaps [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url]'s favorite." 

"She has a mind for suspicion and observation that makes others uneasy. We who operate within the confines of the law have nothing to fear, of course." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>56</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I will not pretend that I find the company of others enjoyable or even bearable at most times. But you are a Fatebinder after my own mind, [Player Name], which makes you worthy above others. I admit, I find your insights often desultory and troubling. All the same, I am pleased that we share this office."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>57</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Moramus of the Mire, The Archon of Fungus, produced most of the flora in the swampland of Nettlebog. A stooped hermit who rather resembled a dapperling, he was never once reported to have left his swamp. Some believe he still lives within the land, though there's been no sighting of him in nearly three hundred years."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>58</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I want to talk about upgrading my Spire."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>60</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Do you know anything about the laws of succession in Stalwart?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>61</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The realm of mad nationalists to the south? Their customs are beyond my purview, but you might ask another of our brood. I know that Calio has been looking into Tiers history with interest."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>62</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Naturally, Fatebinder. What would you like to discuss?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>63</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Let's discuss something else."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>64</ID>
      <DefaultText>"As you will."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>65</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Back to my previous questions."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>66</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Of course, go on."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>67</ID>
      <DefaultText>"If I had a stronghold as remote and solitary as your Spire, I would outfit it with a library. Never let yourself limit the scope of your education. A few restful hours in the company of research can yield much." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>68</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Yes... I understand you have a library at your disposal. Research to your heart's content, but take care not to become greedy for knowledge beyond our authority. [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] has laws regarding the perusal of forbidden knowledge, and we share the burden of law with every other citizen." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>69</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You've built a library and presumably learned much from it. I have no further recommendations."

"The Spires are remarkable. Use them wisely, and do not squander the opportunities before you." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>71</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Fatebinder, you return." Rhogalus looks you up and down with an inscrutable expression.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>72</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I have told you all that I wish. If you would tax my time further, ask about something else."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>73</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Farewell."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>74</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I have pondered your impulsive nature. It vexes me constantly. Your support of the [url=glossary:scarlet chorus]Scarlet Chorus[/url] only affirms my belief that you are among the more severe and unpredictable members of our office."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>75</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You follow an orderly path, regimented and organized. Perhaps too orderly for our station, but that is neither here nor there if you execute your job with wisdom."

"Be sure you don't stray to the path of chaos. Down that way lies rebellion." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>76</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Whatever it may have been, it is reduced of late." Rhogalus pierces you with a severe look. "No matter why you lent your favor to the Southern barbarians, it has cast you in the darkest suspicion. Be advised, Fatebinder - your objectivity is in question. We will be watching." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>77</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You take liberties with the freedom [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url] offers us. In spite of that, your objectivity is beyond question. You would, I think, execute plaintiff and defendant if neither was worthy in your eyes."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>78</ID>
      <DefaultText>"This is the hub of trade and commerce. Claim the markets and the people will follow." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>79</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Stalwart is also worth mention, for it comprises the whole of the southern-most Tier, and proves the toughest and most defensible of the Realms. It is often said that the other Realms will not fall while Stalwart yet stands."

"The local army wages bitter war against the [url=glossary:disfavored]Disfavored[/url], though the [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url] of Storms has cut off the best of their defenses. It is only a matter of time before Stalwart falls." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>80</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What can you tell me of magic?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>82</ID>
      <DefaultText>"There is much I could teach you, [Player Name]." The Fatebinder gazes at you, his eyes narrowed in contemplation. "Given your recent actions, I think the magic of healing will be of the most use to you. Follow along as I scribe the Sigil of Restoration. With enough practice, you will learn to harness its power."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>83</ID>
      <DefaultText>Rhogalus begins scribing a magic sigil in the air. As his hand moves, lines of light form behind his fingers. You copy his motions repeatedly, focusing on the shape you are creating. Eventually your fingers warm as they channel the magic of restoration.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>87</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm not certain that even [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] could have killed the Adjudicator. He was as much an idea, a philosophy, a way of thinking as he was an Archon. Yet somehow you managed." Rhogalus taps his chin with interest.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>88</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Compelled the Adjudicator himself to kneel, did you?" Rhogalus grins. "Impressive work. The last person who did that... well, enough said." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>91</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Ashe has fallen, then. Better that he died in the pursuit of war than some undignified bed, surrounded by weeping mourners."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>92</ID>
      <DefaultText>"If you must hold onto Ashe, keep him in line. Just remember that you are the third master to whom he's sworn his life and fealty."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>94</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Better for all our sakes that [url=glossary:the voices of nerat]the Voices of Nerat[/url] left this world. I always thought that [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] used him to thin the herd, and that anyone in the hierarchy was fair game. Speculation, of course."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>95</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I don't know how you plan on keeping [url=glossary:the voices of nerat]the Voices of Nerat[/url] in line, but that shall be your burden to shoulder. Just don't let him anywhere near me."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>96</ID>
      <DefaultText>"How do you think the Court will fare without [url=glossary:bleden mark]Bleden Mark[/url]?" </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>97</ID>
      <DefaultText>"[url=glossary:bleden mark]Bleden Mark[/url] is under my control. What should I do with him?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>98</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Better than ever, I hope. Without the dependable aid of an unkillable assassin, I'm sure we'll stumble along the way. The Court itself will have to be stronger if it expects to survive, and that sort of change is always welcome."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>99</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm torn up over how to answer that question. You should keep him busy enough that he doesn't grow stagnant and weary, but you shouldn't rely on him so much that his delusion of independence gets even worse than it already is."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
